prove:
    prop p(a, b)
    prop q(a, b)

    know $p(1, 2) or $q(1, 2)

    $p(1, 2) or $q(1, 2)

prove:
    prop p(a, b, c)
    prop q(a, b, c)

    know $p(1, 2, 3) or $q(1, 2, 3)

    let a, b, c R:
        a = 1
        b = 2
        c = 3

    $p(a, b, c) or $q(a, b, c)

prove:
    prop p(a, b)
    prop q(a, b)

    know:
        forall a, b R:
            $p(a, b) or $q(a, b)

    $p(1, 2) or $q(1, 2)

prove:
    prop p(a, b)

    $p(a, b) or not $p(b, a)